node.text:
“Without Brooklyn there would be no Flipp.” Flipp Dinero stops by FCNY to perform live for Flight Club Fridays. The Brooklyn rapper explains how his trials & tribulations have molded him, further contributing to his rounded understanding of music. Flipp developed his eclectic taste in music from being open to diverse sounds growing up, ultimately forming the melodic identity which led him to earning his first multi-platinum certification from the RIAA. To conclude the evening, Flipp gave us an intimate performance of his hit record "Leave Me Alone." Producer/Editor - Derek Putlak
Director of Photography - Marshall Douglis
Camera Operator - Taylor Washington

node.title: Flight Club Fridays - Flipp Dinero Performs "Leave Me Alone" Live @ FCNY

node.text:
“Your feet represent you and how you’re feeling at the current time.” Flipp Dinero stops by FCNY to perform live for Flight Club Fridays. The Brooklyn rapper describes his hometown as “very creative” and “emotion-packed” while checking out FCNY’s grail case – mentioning his infatuation with Jordans and how he always dreamed of having the Air Jordan 6 Retro NRG “Green Suede Gatorade” sneakers while on tour. Flipp then performed his hit songs "Feelin Like" and "I Do" to an intimate crowd. 
Producer/Editor - Derek Putlak 
Director of Photography - Marshall Douglis 
Camera Operator - Taylor Washington

node.title: Flight Club Fridays - Flipp Dinero Performs "Feeling Like" Live @ FCNY

node.text: The Air Force 180 'Olympic' showcases the OG colorway worn by Charles Barkley, who was the Dream Team’s leading scorer during their historic run at the 1992 Summer Olympics. Sporting a combination of leather and nubuck throughout its upper, the patriotic sneaker features Varsity Red, white and navy blue accents, as hits of Metallic Gold embellish the tongue and midfoot strap. A speckled, gold gradient extends across the midsole, giving way to the visible 180 Max Air unit encased in the heel.

node.text:
Before Nike SB ever existed, Nike introduced one of the most vibrant Dunks in history as a Japanese exclusive under its experimental Pro B line.

The Viotech Dunk is often considered as part of the ‘Ugly Duckling’ pack due to its similar use of clashing colors, premium suede and mesh tongue. “Viotech” is a color term created by Nike that refers to a particular shade of purple, and it has been used on some of the most iconic releases including the Air Max 1 B x atmos and the Air Trainer 3.

The Flight Club Heritage Collection is an explorative series that revisits the past and rediscovers the golden era of sneakers. Shop history now at Flight Club.

node.text: The Yeezy Foam Runner 'Ochre' arrives in an earthy, clay pigment throughout its lightweight, EVA foam construction, bringing a monochromatic style to the one-piece silhouette. The shoe is perforated with circular vents for enhanced breathability, while a textured insole ensures a comfortable ride.

node.text: The Dunk Low 'White University Red' brings a familiar color treatment to the basketball silhouette, sporting a bright red base contrasted by white leather overlays. Perforations over the toe box provide enhanced breathability, while a University Red rubber outsole supplies traction underfoot.

node.text: Kanye West’s innovative stint with Nike officially began in April 2009 with the release of the Air Yeezy – a new silhouette inspired by various archival sneakers from Nike’s catalog, notably the AJ3, AJ4 and Air Tech Challenge 2. The first of three colorways to hit the streets, the Air Yeezy 'Zen' sports a charcoal leather upper with flashes of hot pink and orange over the tongue and inner lining. A textured ‘Y’ pattern appears over the suede mudguard and patent leather midfoot strap extending across the shoe, while a re-engineered, glow-in-the-dark outsole completes the look.

node.text: 15 years after its original release, the Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Lightning' 2021 brings back the Tour Yellow colorway inspired by Michael Jordan’s motorsports team. Built with a premium nubuck construction, the shoe’s upper is contrasted by black mesh and dark grey overlays along the tongue, outsole and Jumpman logo located on the heel. Visible Air cushioning arrives via a white, polyurethane midsole, giving way to a rubber outsole with herringbone traction.

node.text: Originally debuted in 1995, the Air Zoom Flight 95 was popularized by Jason Kidd during his first NBA season, in which he led the league in triple doubles and won Rookie of the Year. Re-released in honor of the silhouette’s 20th Anniversary, the Air Zoom Flight 95 'Black Metallic Silver' 2015 sports a premium nubuck upper with signature carbon fiber overlays, accented by circular Zoom pods extending from the midsole to the sidewall. Swoosh embroidery appears over the lateral side, as Zoom Air tech provides cushioning underfoot.

node.text: A three-way collaboration featuring two of Jordan Brand’s most influential cohorts, the fragment design x Travis Scott x Air Jordan 1 Retro High emerges in a white tumbled leather base with Military Blue overlays along the toe box, collar and outsole. The sneaker takes color-blocking elements from Hiroshi Fujiwara’s 2014 AJ1 collab, while Travis Scott’s imprints appear in an inverted Swoosh and hidden heel pouch. Cactus Jack’s smiley face logo and fragment’s signature lightning bolt leave their mark on the left and right heel respectively, as a pre-yellowed midsole supplies Nike Air cushioning underfoot.

node.text:
Michael Jordan rejoined the NBA in the 2001-2002 season and Jordan Brand created an all-new shoe for his return. Referencing his mid-air wizardry, the Air Jordan 17 was inspired by his improvisational nature whenever he took flight and the smooth, sophisticated style of jazz music. 

They came equipped with a large volume Air bag in the heel, achieved through a blow-molded process, a full-length shank plate and a TPU heel stabilizer, making this the most expensive Air Jordan at the time.

The Flight Club Heritage Collection is an explorative series that revisits the past and rediscovers the golden era of sneakers. Shop history now at Flight Club.

node.text: Renewing the collaboration between Converse and the UK-based sneaker boutique, the Offspring x Chuck 70 High 'Paisley Patchwork’ features a vibrant, multi-colored canvas upper with the outsole to match. Red, black, and grey overlays are contrasted by visible stitching throughout the shoe, while a beige rubber outsole provides traction underfoot.

node.text: Virgil Abloh merges his signature design system with one of Nike’s most innovative running shoes to create the Off-White x Air Zoom Tempo Next% ‘Black.’ Constructed with a breathable and lightweight knit, the performance runner features a black base with contrasting white accents along the laces and painted-on Swoosh. Scream Green overlays appear throughout the tongue and outsole, the latter equipped with racing-inspired rubber spikes for next-level traction.

node.text: The Wmns Lahar Low 'Wheat' offers a street-ready revamp to the original Lahar Escape Boot – Nike’s vintage hiking shoes from 1989. Seated atop a speckled black midsole equipped with Nike Air cushioning, the sneaker is clad in tan suede with jet black overlays throughout the Swoosh, outsole and utility pull tab located on the heel.
